name aidisclose
category Package
revision 79452
shortdesc Generate disclosure statements and checklists for the use of generative AI
longdesc This package provides a standardized, transparent way to
longdesc declare the use of generative artificial intelligence (AI)
longdesc tools in academic, technical, and professional documents. It
longdesc implements an extension of the GAIDeT (Generative AI Delegation
longdesc Taxonomy), letting authors mark which tasks were delegated to
longdesc AI, list the tools used (or state that none were), add optional
longdesc numbered or unnumbered comments, and automatically typeset a
longdesc formatted disclosure section or chapter with a task-based
longdesc checklist. Configuration uses a key-value interface, and
longdesc citations for the taxonomy and the package can be managed
longdesc automatically. The package detects the document language
longdesc through babel or polyglossia and ships translations for
longdesc fourteen languages, falling back to English. A companion web
longdesc generator/configurator is available at https://aidisclose.org.
